<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
(Anonymous): Reflection doesn't reflect arrows/bolts/magic from traps.  Also, reflection seems 'broken' after loading savefile, and must be restarted by removing and rewearing item granting reflection. <p>
<strong><a class="nonexistent" href="./XandorTikroth">XandorTikroth</a></strong>: Well, as for the traps, it's not like you know that they're coming, especially if you just hit one that you didn't sense before.  Perhaps there should be two rules: 
</p>
<p>
1) If you step onto a previously unsensed trap that fires (say) a Mana Bolt at you, if you have reflection, it should have a very good chance to hit you since you were "surprised" by it 
</p>
<p>
2) If you step onto a trap as a result of having already sensed it, but accidentally triggering it due to a failed attempt at disarming it, you should have a 1/2 to a 2/3 chance of reflecting it (I also think that maybe this should be related to the weight of the sheild and the str/dex of the character) 
</p>
<p>
I don't know how hard it would be to implement these rules, or even if you can, but it would be interesting to see.  I think also that if your character is wearing the Ring of Precognition, that it should grant the wearer knowledge of the traps on that level, since it gives knowledge of other stuff... 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./TobiasParker">TobiasParker</a></strong>:  Isn't "Reflection" more of an enchantment that is placed on a shield....i mean if it was dependent on the characters ability to see and actually **block** the incoming projectile than how would amulets of reflection work.  Maybe we could just make all shields (re)deflect projectiles based on their size.  For example where the (xx%) is chance to deflect projectile, small shield[+2 +4](2%) or Large Shield of reflection [+5 +5] (25%) or even the dark elven shield of standing out like a sore thumb(-5 -10) (-50%), making the person **easier** to hit 
</p>
</div><div id="footer">


